<item>
            <title>[LU-16893] Fix cfs_force_sig(sig, task) deadlock on 5.3 and later kernels.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16893</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When HAVE_FORCE_SIG_WITH_TASK is not available cfs_force_sig() is used.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However cfs_force_sig holds a spin lock on &apos;siglock&apos;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;#define cfs_force_sig(sig, task) \
do { \
unsigned long flags;\
\
spin_lock_irqsave(&amp;amp;task-&amp;gt;sighand-&amp;gt;siglock, flags);\
task-&amp;gt;sighand-&amp;gt;action[sig - 1].sa.sa_handler = SIG_DFL;\
send_sig(sig, task, 1);\
spin_unlock_irqrestore(&amp;amp;task-&amp;gt;sighand-&amp;gt;siglock, flags);&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;\
} while (0)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This causes a dead lock on &apos;siglock&apos; as do_send_sig_info also takes the same lock.&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;cfs_force_sig(sig, task)
&#160; -&amp;gt; spin_lock_irqsave(&amp;amp;task-&amp;gt;sighand-&amp;gt;siglock, flags); \
&#160; &#160; -&amp;gt; send_sig(.., task,..)
&#160; &#160; &#160;-&amp;gt; send_sig_info(.., task)
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;-&amp;gt; do_send_sig_info(..., task)
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;-&amp;gt; lock_task_sighand(task)
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;-&amp;gt; __lock_task_sighand(task, flags)
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; {
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; sighand = rcu_dereference(task-&amp;gt;sighand);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; spin_lock_irqsave(&amp;amp;sighand-&amp;gt;siglock, *flags);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; ...
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; }&#160;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cfs_force_sig() should release the spin lock before calling send_sig()&lt;/p&gt;</description>
